<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,152,1447]" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1346,1372]" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
A smaller bicolorous species generally fitting with the smaller bicolorous species: 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1394,1347,1372]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corvi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1307,1394,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">T. corvi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="15" pageNumber="60" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Heller. The" authorityName="Heller. The" box="[250,564,1384,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsericea">
<emphasis box="[250,415,1384,1409]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="60">T. subsericea</emphasis>
Heller. The
</taxonomicName>
highly modified bituberculate female ventrite 
<number box="[1149,1164,1384,1410]" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
and simple ventrite 
<number box="[1421,1436,1384,1410]" pageId="15" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
separate this species from its close allies. Both sexes treated. Named for the constellation Scorpius.
</paragraph>
